Now I understand the bug. In the buggy `dup_user_cpus_ptr`, when `src->user_cpus_ptr` is NULL (freed by concurrent `do_set_cpus_allowed`), the function returns 0 **without clearing `dst->user_cpus_ptr`** — which still holds the stale pointer from `dup_task_struct`. The fix adds `dst->user_cpus_ptr = NULL` at the start.

I'll demonstrate this by setting up the race state and calling `dup_user_cpus_ptr` directly.

